entry.name: llm_multistep_message_drop
entry.text: MPGW resources exhausted. Unable to deliver message on topic: %s
entry.description: MPGW resources exhausted. Unable to deliver message
entry.suggestion: Reduce the transmitter send rate or alter the configuration to reduce the memory requirements. This message is only logged every 30 seconds for performance reasons. To verify the number of messages being dropped, use the LLM status provider to compare LLM RLM Route object throughput to that of the throughput seen on the LLM Policy object that references the LLM RLM Route route object.

entry.name: trv_no_backend_reqreply_setup
entry.text: TIBCO RV request/reply flow through Multi-Protocol Gateway could not be setup
entry.description: TIBCO RV request/reply flow through Multi-Protocol Gateway could not be setup. This occurs when a TIBCO RV TLM route has been configured for request/reply flows and the back end URL for the Multi-Protocol Gateway is configured to be a TIBCO RV URL, (dptibrv:///) but the EnableReply query parameter is not enabled.
entry.suggestion: If request/reply flows are required, and the backend URL for a Multi-Protocol Gateway is a TIBCO RV URL, use the TIBCO RV URL builder to turn on the EnableReply query parameter.

entry.name: trv_multistep_message_drop
entry.text: MPGW resources exhausted. Unable to deliver message on subject: %s
entry.description: MPGW resources exhausted. Unable to deliver message.
entry.suggestion: Reduce the transmitter send rate or alter the configuration to reduce the memory requirements. This message is only logged every 30 seconds for performance reasons. To verify the number of messages being dropped, use the TIBCO RV status provider to compare TIBCO RV TLM Route object throughput to that of the throughput seen on the TIBCO RV Policy object that references the TIBCO RV TLM Route route object.

entry.suggestion: Make sure the LLM Instance has been started. See the LLM online help and the LLM Developers Guide, including the link to the LLM 2.2 Information Center, for additional information on configuring LLM.

entry.name: llmd9103
entry.text: LLMD9103E The system is low on resources. TIBCO RV traffic is being throttled.
entry.description: The system is low on resources. New TIBCO RV work requests received by the system will not be processed. Normal processing will resume once resources become available.
entry.suggestion: Situations like these usually arise when there are fast producers of TIBCO RV traffic paired with slow consumers.

entry.name: llmd9104
entry.text: LLMD9104E System resources are once again available. TIBCO RV traffic is no longer being throttled.
entry.description: Resources are once again available and the system is now able to process new TIBCO RV work requests.
entry.suggestion: See the XM70 online help and the XM70 Developers Guide for additional information on configuring TIBCO RV on the XM70.

entry.name: llmd9115
entry.text: LLMD9115E Unable to obtain ledger file lock.
entry.description: The ledger file either does not exist or is in use by another TIBCO RV Route or Policy.
entry.suggestion: Verify that no other appliances in the network contain identically configured TIBCO RV Route or Policy objects.

entry.name: trvcm_duplicate_name
entry.text: A reusable name (%1$s) exists on another network interface (%2$s).
entry.description: A duplicate reusable name (either certified message name or relay agent name) was found. The reusable names of both a TIBCO RV Policy and TIBCO RV Route must be unique on the same network.
entry.suggestion: Verify the duplicate reusable names are in fact on different networks. Different network interfaces do not necessarily mean different networks. To avoid potential conflicts, specify a unique reusable name.
